In 1971, Bolivian general Hugo Banzer deposed socialist president Juan José Torres, who would later be assassinated on Videla's Argentina. Banzer would democratically return to office in 1997. The Peruvian Military Junta in 1968 grabbed power from President Fernando Belaúnde Terry and replaced him with General Juan Velasco Alvarado before he himself was deposed by General Francisco Morales-Bermúdez.[34]
